<p>Perfect!</p>
<p>Go back to the form. Uncheck one of the genuses and check a new one. When we submit,
it <em>should</em> call <code>addStudiedGenus()</code> once for the new checkbox and <code>removeStudiedGenus()</code>
once for the box we unchecked.</p>
<p>Ok, hit update! Hmm, it <em>looked</em> successful... but it still didn't actually work.
And that's expected! We just setup a cool little system where the form component calls
our adder and remover methods to update the <code>studiedGenuses</code> property. But... this hasn't
really changed anything: we're still not setting the <em>owning</em> side of the relationship.</p>
<p>But, we're just <em>one</em> small step from doing that.</p>

    
